Teaching Function of Behavior [id=fba2_function_teaching]
------------------------------

JJ: Whew, thank you for the refresher. I needed that.

Lin: Me too. Lianne also said a couple of other things during our last class. She said that if the function is for attention or tangibles, it usually involves positive reinforcement. If the function is escape, it typically involves negative reinforcement. And for sensory, it can be either one.

Annie: I think it would really help my brain if we put all these concepts together. I think AI would help here.

